title: Jupyter-Notebook and Jupyter-Lab crash on deeplabcut import
body:
Thanks for opening this issue, and thanks for using DeepLabCut (we hope you are enjoying it ;). Please fill out the template completely, including the full "traceback" and input code that you ran to hit this error. **Your Operating system and DeepLabCut version** MacOS Big Sur (11.1), Anaconda Env, DeepLabCut2.1.10 **Describe the problem** I'm trying to run one of the example notebooks in jupyter-notebook / jupyter-lab (both break). As soon as I run ```import deeplabcut``` I get the following message in the browser ![Screen Shot 2021-02-03 at 1 26 16 PM](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/16822502/106811583-68055300-6623-11eb-8270-bd4802bd72f9.png) and the following log in terminal: ```[I 2021-02-03 13:25:22.213 ServerApp] KernelRestarter: restarting kernel (1/5), keep random ports``` I've attempted install manually and with the provided env file (cpu based). I'm not having this problem with any other "standard" package I attempt to import. Please place code inside this:
